    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="to"
                            >Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 29, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190. In response to inquiry which <persName corresp="#p_AJ1">Avenol</persName>
                    forwarded to <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Norman Davis</persName> regarding
                    addition of Indian representative to the Preparatory Committee, both <persName
                        corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SFM1"
                        >Sackett</persName> are prepared to consent to the addition. But in cable
                    just received from <persName corresp="#p_CHM1">Cochran</persName> in Paris it
                    would appear that <persName corresp="#p_FL1">Fraser</persName> still believes
                    there is some uncertainty as to whether the Organizing Committee finally decided
                    to add a Chinese representative to full membership on the Committee.</p>
                <p>It has been <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>’s understanding and ours
                    that full agreement had been reached on this point. <persName corresp="#p_DNH1"
                        >Davis</persName> states that the first record of the proceedings of the
                    Organizing Committee was erroneous in that it stated that the Chinese expert was
                    to attend only on the silver question but <persName corresp="#p_DNH1"
                        >Davis</persName> talked with <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John
                        Simon</persName> and this was corrected.</p>
                <p>Please see <persName corresp="#p_AJ1">Avenol</persName> and ascertain whether the
                    appointment of a Chinese expert in full capacity is settled as we understand. If
                    so you may please inform him that the American representatives have no objection
                    to the appointment of an Indian representative. If <pb facs="0964" n="844"
                        xml:id="pg_844"/> there is still any question regarding the appointment of
                    the Chinese in full capacity withhold any statement as regards the Indian
                    representative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
